00:41:32.830 --> 00:41:35.850
like how those concerns
of affect, will they too

00:41:35.850 --> 00:41:38.290
or don't play to, how you're
viewing emotion and [inaudible]?

00:41:38.290 --> 00:41:39.730
&gt;&gt; Anne Burkus-Chasson: In
truth, I have read affect theory

00:41:39.730 --> 00:41:43.390
but I have not -- this is a
recent discovery, frankly.

00:41:43.390 --> 00:41:48.200
I only in the last month
connected Chen Hongshou's

00:41:48.200 --> 00:41:51.390
drunkard with that
very famous prose text.

00:41:51.390 --> 00:41:52.690
And so, I in fact, no.

00:41:52.690 --> 00:41:54.090
In short. No I have
not connected it

00:41:54.090 --> 00:41:55.580
with other writings on affect.

00:41:55.580 --> 00:41:57.960
I was very behind in
the readings on emotion.

00:41:57.960 --> 00:42:00.380
And there has been just
recently, as I mentioned,

00:42:00.380 --> 00:42:04.010
quite a bit of work on
emotion on Chinese literature.

00:42:04.010 --> 00:42:08.790
And it was actually through
that reading that I, of course,

00:42:08.790 --> 00:42:11.330
it's text of Fan Zhongyan
is extremely famous.

00:42:11.330 --> 00:42:12.950
So, there've been
multiple essays written

00:42:12.950 --> 00:42:15.020
about how melancholy
is defined in China.

00:42:15.020 --> 00:42:16.510
And it was always
referred to that text.

00:42:16.510 --> 00:42:19.540
And then when I thought
about Chen's the letter

00:42:19.540 --> 00:42:24.280
and his concern about the
bandits and the invasions,

00:42:24.280 --> 00:42:25.890
incursions into the
Chinese territory,

00:42:25.890 --> 00:42:27.190
I went in that direction.

00:42:27.190 --> 00:42:28.490
But affect theory, no.

00:42:28.490 --> 00:42:29.790
I haven't gone there, yet.

00:42:29.790 --> 00:42:31.090
I may. But I'm most
familiar with affect theory,

00:42:31.090 --> 00:42:32.390
having written a review
of Jonathan Hayes book

00:42:32.390 --> 00:42:33.690
on the sensualist surface
-- what is it called?

00:42:33.690 --> 00:42:36.190
Some of you would know that.

00:42:36.190 --> 00:42:38.590
You two would know.

00:42:38.590 --> 00:42:39.890
[Laughs, inaudible response].

00:42:39.890 --> 00:42:41.190
The Sensuist Serf [assumed
spelling] -- [laughs].

00:42:41.190 --> 00:42:44.060
They had to read it, I know.

00:42:44.060 --> 00:42:50.950
So, that was more about
wanting to touch and wanting

00:42:50.950 --> 00:42:52.250
to touch the ceramics.

00:42:52.250 --> 00:42:53.930
That is how he uses it.

00:42:53.930 --> 00:42:58.740
And the theorists whom he
cites are engaged with that.

00:42:58.740 --> 00:43:02.290
So, this is not where
I was going.

00:43:02.290 --> 00:43:05.790
In terms of going
to touch something.

00:43:05.790 --> 00:43:08.280
Is that -- did I
answer your question?

00:43:08.280 --> 00:43:09.580
Okay. Good.

00:43:09.580 --> 00:43:11.510
Yes.

